# Backend (NestJS + SQLite)

## Folder structure

```
backend/src/
  main.ts              # bootstrap + SwaggerModule.setup
  app.module.ts
  todos/
    todos.module.ts
    todos.controller.ts
    todos.service.ts
    dto/
    entities/
  categories/
    categories.module.ts
    categories.controller.ts
    categories.service.ts
  common/
    filters/           # HttpExceptionFilter — consistent JSON shape
    pipes/
    constants/         # MAX_TASKS_PER_CATEGORY = 5
```

## Stack

- NestJS feature modules: controller → service → repository/entity; no fat controllers
- SQLite via TypeORM
- Swagger via `@nestjs/swagger` — `@ApiTags`, `@ApiOperation`, `@ApiResponse` on every endpoint; `@ApiProperty` on DTOs; UI at `/api` (auto-updated from decorators, no manual spec files)
- `class-validator` on DTOs + global `ValidationPipe`

## Endpoints

| Method | Path | Notes |
|--------|------|-------|
| POST | `/todos` | 400 if category has 5 tasks |
| GET | `/todos?category=` | optional filter |
| PATCH | `/todos/:id` | update completed status |
| DELETE | `/todos/:id` | hard delete |
| GET | `/categories` | list for dropdown |

## Error contract

Every failure returns frontend-displayable JSON:

```json
{ "statusCode": 400, "message": "Category \"Work\" already has 5 tasks.", "error": "Bad Request" }
```

- Use `BadRequestException('specific message')` in services
- Global exception filter for unexpected errors → `{ statusCode: 500, message: 'Internal server error' }`
- Document error cases with `@ApiResponse({ status: 400, description: '...' })`
